<p>
  If you've ever pasted a URL into a browser and seen <code>%20</code> where a space should be, or watched an API call fail because a query parameter contained an ampersand, you've encountered URL encoding. Also known as percent-encoding, it's the mechanism that lets URLs carry special characters safely across the internet.
</p>

